Meet <b>Kimmy707</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Kimmy707 has lived in Millsberry since May 15, 2005, and recently celebrated her 2-year anniversary as a citizen! She invited all her friends to her home at <a href='/home/?user=kimmy707'>12139 Bunker Park</a> where they partied before walking from Metro Park to the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/arcade.phtml">arcade</a>.<br><br>Kimmy707 is a girl you should know. She's a great student who especially loves biology. She has been thinking of continuing to study biology in hopes of becoming a doctor. We certainly think she has the right mix of compassion, intelligence and common sense to be an amazing physician!<br><br>When she isn't running experiments in the Millsberry Academy <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/academy/lab/">lab</a>, you can find her chatting with Hidaka Sensei at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/communitycenter/dojo/">dojo</a>, or listening to rap, R&B, or pop at home. She's very interested in the philosophy behind martial arts, and is also interested in the process of making music. She's someone who tries hard to understand the history and thinking behind the things she enjoys.<br><br>If you want to send her a 2-year anniversary gift, make it something violet or blue&mdash;her favorite colors. Thanks for being a good citizen, Kimmy707, and congratulations on being named Citizen of the Week!<br></div>
